[2]
Date: 3 Jul 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Clic RBS.com [edited]
<http://www.clicrbs.com.br/default.jsp?uf=1&local=1&tab=00001&newsID=a64476.htm&subTab=00000>

Vermicide is the probable cause of tetanus in Gaucho [Rio Grande do Sul]
animals. The first results of tests on material collected from cattle and
sheep that died of tetanus during the last 3 weeks in the municipalities of
Sao Gabriel, Rosario do Sul and Heral, led [investigators to suspect] a
brand of vermicide. More than 300 animals died.
The official results will be released in the next few days by the Regional
Area Animal Laboratory (LARA) of the Ministry of Agriculture. The
bacteriologist Joaquim Fernandes of the Federal University of Rio Grande do
Sul said that the anti-tetanus serum [would resolve] the problem if given
early on, during the first symptoms of the disease.
­­
