[3]
Date: 2 Jul 2001 07:36
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Clic RBS.com [edited]
<http://www.clicrbs.com.br/default.jsp?uf=1&local=1&tab=00002&newsID=a64382.htm&subTab=200>

The Federal University of Rio Grande do Sul (UFRGS) should announce the
results of the pathology exams to identify the causes of tetanus which
affected 255 cattle on 3 properties [ranches] since 11 Jun 2001.
The Federal University of Pelotas (UFPel) will make public the [results of
tests] conducted on 55 sheep that died from the same disease in the
municipality of Pedras Altas.
If the cause is definitely a vermicide, the state government will solicit
the Ministry of Agriculture to remove the product from the market.
